### Description

When importing a json file using `import('file.json')` in an CLi application, the JSON returned does not include the root keys that have a dash in their name.

Consider the following JSON:
```json
{
  "withoutdash": "Without dash, OK",
  "with-dash": "With dash, OK",
  "nested": {
    "withoutdash": "Nested without dash, OK",
    "with-dash": "Nested with dash, OK"
  }
}
```

loaded in a component dynamically:
```ts
  jsonContent: any;

  async show() {
    const fileName = 'test';
    this.jsonContent = await import(`./${fileName}.json`);
  }
```

and then displayed:
```html
<button (click)="show()">Load and show JSON content</button>

@if (jsonContent) {
<h1>Whole object</h1>
<pre>{{ jsonContent | json }}</pre>

<h1>Default property</h1>
<pre>{{ jsonContent.default | json }}</pre>
}
```

The whole object displays (no `with-dash` root key):
```json
{
  "default": {
    "withoutdash": "Without dash, OK",
    "with-dash": "With dash, OK",
    "nested": {
      "withoutdash": "Nested without dash, OK",
      "with-dash": "Nested with dash, OK"
    }
  },
  "nested": {
    "withoutdash": "Nested without dash, OK",
    "with-dash": "Nested with dash, OK"
  },
  "withoutdash": "Without dash, OK"
}
```

whereas the default content is correct:
```json
{
  "withoutdash": "Without dash, OK",
  "with-dash": "With dash, OK",
  "nested": {
    "withoutdash": "Nested without dash, OK",
    "with-dash": "Nested with dash, OK"
  }
}
```

### Minimal Reproduction

See https://stackblitz.com/edit/stackblitz-starters-dg68rk?file=json-loading-bug%2Fsrc%2Fapp%2Fapp.component.html

Run:
```
cd json-loading-bug/
npm i
npm run start
```

